{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VLhioJjbQYS8GCDJBYAcbu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent Exploration Notes\n     2→\n     3→## Key Files & Roles\n     4→\n     5→- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared runtime library for all agents. Provides env defaults, step timing, output helpers, cleanup trap, workflow lock, and dependency checking via `need()`.\n     6→- `skills/bash-agent/scripts/bash-agent.sh`: multi-scope baseline for `CHANGED_FILES` filtering and output contract.\n     7→- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: shared-lib-backed orchestration for heavy multi-step outputs and failure aggregation.\n     8→- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: domain-specific step toggles and scope mapping for source files.\n     9→- `skills/helm-agent/` (to be added): new Helm chart runner with chart discovery + per-step toggles.\n    10→- `skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh`: single-step discovery/scoping example, including skip behavior for missing optional directories.\n    11→- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: fallback-tool execution pattern and scoped target filtering for file-based steps.\n    12→- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: lock + non-mutating safety patterns plus optional tooling behavior.\n    13→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: centralized test runner; invokes shellcheck then executes each `scenario.env` fixture.\n    14→- `tests/<agent>/clean/` and `tests/<agent>/issues/`: minimal scenario fixtures for deterministic pass/fail behavior.\n    15→- `tests/helm-agent/` (to be added): chart fixtures for linting/render validation and scoped chart discovery.\n    16→- `install.sh`: installer registry/discovery for skills and optional dependency checks.\n    17→- `README.md`: canonical user-facing agent catalog and usage examples.\n    18→- `.ralph/specs/06-helm-agent.md`: helm acceptance criteria and required edge-case behavior (`CHART_DIR`, `CHANGED_FILES`, skip semantics).\n    19→- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: required files and workflow for adding a new agent.\n    20→- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: completion criteria for output contract, knobs, docs, and tests.\n    21→\n    22→## Patterns & Conventions\n    23→\n    24→- Bash scripts are Bash 3.2-compatible and begin with `#!/usr/bin/env bash` plus `set -euo pipefail`.\n    25→- Shared helpers are imported via `SCRIPT_DIR/../../../lib/x-agent-common.sh`; no duplicated boilerplate.\n    26→- Structured output is mandatory: each step prints `Step`, `Result`, optional `Fix`, `Full log`, and timing; final output includes `Overall` and `Logs`.\n    27→- Universal knobs are expected: `RUN_<STEP>`, `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, and `CHANGED_FILES`.\n    28→- CLI contracts require `help`/`--help`/`-h` before mandatory tool checks, `all` default, and explicit command dispatch.\n    29→- `RUN_*` and scope checks should be no-op-friendly, preserving deterministic SKIP paths where project content is missing.\n    30→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` resolves paths by directory scan and skips scenarios missing `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n    31→- `--fail-fast` is enforced with a central `should_continue()` guard around multi-step `all` flows.\n    32→\n    33→## Database Schema\n    34→\n    35→No database is used.\n    36→\n    37→## Test Infrastructure\n    38→\n    39→- Scenario discovery is filesystem-based using `find tests -name scenario.env`.\n    40→- Each scenario has a `scenario.env` with `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, optional `RUN_ARGS`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n    41→- Scenario tests use clean/issues fixtures with hardcoded fixtures per agent and exit-code assertions.\n    42→- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` also runs shellcheck on project scripts, with required severity threshold in CI.\n    43→- `.ralph/specs/*.md` encode each spec’s FR checklist; previous iterations highlight recurring gap coverage around scoped-edge cases.\n    44→\n    45→## Architecture & Data Flow\n    46→\n    47→- Invocation enters via `skills/<agent>/scripts/<agent>-agent.sh` and goes through: `help/args -> need checks -> setup_outdir/lock -> discovery/scope -> per-step execution -> final `print_overall`.\n    48→- Shared library calls are centralized for lifecycle and formatting; agent scripts contain only domain logic.\n    49→- Discovery patterns vary by agent: file extensions, directory conventions, and optional explicit overrides like `CHART_DIR` (helm) or tool-specific root settings.\n    50→- Scenario execution flow: discover scenarios, run script from fixture dir, compare observed exit code with `EXPECT_EXIT`, and stream logs on mismatch.\n    51→- Security and data-access boundary is local filesystem only; avoid unsafe path expansion and quote discovered paths before execution.\n    52→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be0e30e7-8817-4b77-ad57-f2dbd38ea5b9","uuid":"793b6848-3e4f-4535-9b67-bea0b8ff2a14","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","content":"# x-agent Exploration Notes\n\n## Key Files & Roles\n\n- `lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared runtime library for all agents. Provides env defaults, step timing, output helpers, cleanup trap, workflow lock, and dependency checking via `need()`.\n- `skills/bash-agent/scripts/bash-agent.sh`: multi-scope baseline for `CHANGED_FILES` filtering and output contract.\n- `skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh`: shared-lib-backed orchestration for heavy multi-step outputs and failure aggregation.\n- `skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh`: domain-specific step toggles and scope mapping for source files.\n- `skills/helm-agent/` (to be added): new Helm chart runner with chart discovery + per-step toggles.\n- `skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh`: single-step discovery/scoping example, including skip behavior for missing optional directories.\n- `skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh`: fallback-tool execution pattern and scoped target filtering for file-based steps.\n- `skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh`: lock + non-mutating safety patterns plus optional tooling behavior.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh`: centralized test runner; invokes shellcheck then executes each `scenario.env` fixture.\n- `tests/<agent>/clean/` and `tests/<agent>/issues/`: minimal scenario fixtures for deterministic pass/fail behavior.\n- `tests/helm-agent/` (to be added): chart fixtures for linting/render validation and scoped chart discovery.\n- `install.sh`: installer registry/discovery for skills and optional dependency checks.\n- `README.md`: canonical user-facing agent catalog and usage examples.\n- `.ralph/specs/06-helm-agent.md`: helm acceptance criteria and required edge-case behavior (`CHART_DIR`, `CHANGED_FILES`, skip semantics).\n- `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: required files and workflow for adding a new agent.\n- `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: completion criteria for output contract, knobs, docs, and tests.\n\n## Patterns & Conventions\n\n- Bash scripts are Bash 3.2-compatible and begin with `#!/usr/bin/env bash` plus `set -euo pipefail`.\n- Shared helpers are imported via `SCRIPT_DIR/../../../lib/x-agent-common.sh`; no duplicated boilerplate.\n- Structured output is mandatory: each step prints `Step`, `Result`, optional `Fix`, `Full log`, and timing; final output includes `Overall` and `Logs`.\n- Universal knobs are expected: `RUN_<STEP>`, `KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, and `CHANGED_FILES`.\n- CLI contracts require `help`/`--help`/`-h` before mandatory tool checks, `all` default, and explicit command dispatch.\n- `RUN_*` and scope checks should be no-op-friendly, preserving deterministic SKIP paths where project content is missing.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` resolves paths by directory scan and skips scenarios missing `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n- `--fail-fast` is enforced with a central `should_continue()` guard around multi-step `all` flows.\n\n## Database Schema\n\nNo database is used.\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n- Scenario discovery is filesystem-based using `find tests -name scenario.env`.\n- Each scenario has a `scenario.env` with `SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, optional `RUN_ARGS`, and `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n- Scenario tests use clean/issues fixtures with hardcoded fixtures per agent and exit-code assertions.\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` also runs shellcheck on project scripts, with required severity threshold in CI.\n- `.ralph/specs/*.md` encode each spec’s FR checklist; previous iterations highlight recurring gap coverage around scoped-edge cases.\n\n## Architecture & Data Flow\n\n- Invocation enters via `skills/<agent>/scripts/<agent>-agent.sh` and goes through: `help/args -> need checks -> setup_outdir/lock -> discovery/scope -> per-step execution -> final `print_overall`.\n- Shared library calls are centralized for lifecycle and formatting; agent scripts contain only domain logic.\n- Discovery patterns vary by agent: file extensions, directory conventions, and optional explicit overrides like `CHART_DIR` (helm) or tool-specific root settings.\n- Scenario execution flow: discover scenarios, run script from fixture dir, compare observed exit code with `EXPECT_EXIT`, and stream logs on mismatch.\n- Security and data-access boundary is local filesystem only; avoid unsafe path expansion and quote discovered paths before execution.\n","numLines":52,"startLine":1,"totalLines":52}}}
