{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JPshYojnwuVnqXpEgNtkDe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Implementation Checklist\n     2→- [ ] 1. Confirm `AGENTS.md`, `.ralph/task.md`, `.ralph/specs/06-helm-agent.md`, `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`, and `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md` constraints against the current repo state.\n     3→- [ ] 2. Create `skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh` with Bash 3.2-safe header and explicit usage of `set -euo pipefail`.\n     4→- [ ] 3. Source `lib/x-agent-common.sh` via `SCRIPT_DIR/../../../lib` and rely on shared helpers for `step`, timing, output, trap, lock, fail-fast, and `need()`.\n     5→- [ ] 4. Implement required knobs and defaults: `RUN_LINT`, `RUN_TEMPLATE`, `CHART_DIR`, and universal knobs (`KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, `CHANGED_FILES`).\n     6→- [ ] 5. Add `--help`/`help`/`-h` early dispatch and required-tool validation with `need helm` in the non-help execution path.\n     7→- [ ] 6. Implement chart detection resolver with precedence: `CHART_DIR` > `CHANGED_FILES`-derived chart roots > recursive `Chart.yaml` search.\n     8→- [ ] 7. Implement `lint` command as `helm lint` with per-chart iteration, log capture, and strict `Fix: resolve the chart errors above, then re-run: /helm-agent lint`.\n     9→- [ ] 8. Implement `template` command as `helm template` with per-chart iteration, output discard on success, and strict failure log reporting with `Fix: resolve the template errors above, then re-run: /helm-agent template`.\n    10→- [ ] 9. Implement command orchestration for `lint`, `template`, `all` with `RUN_*` toggles, `FAIL_FAST` guard, and `Overall` aggregation.\n    11→- [ ] 10. Add `skills/helm-agent/SKILL.md` with triggers and allowed-tools (including `CHART_DIR=*` and universal knobs).\n    12→- [ ] 11. Add `tests/helm-agent/clean/` scenario fixture and `tests/helm-agent/issues/` scenario fixture with deterministic behavior and `REQUIRED_TOOLS=\"helm\"`.\n    13→- [ ] 12. Add explicit scope/skip tests for Helm chart detection edge cases (`CHANGED_FILES` scope resolution and no `Chart.yaml` skip) using additional scenario directories.\n    14→- [ ] 13. Update `install.sh` to register helm-agent, include optional dependency hints for helm, and include the AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet line.\n    15→- [ ] 14. Update `README.md` with `helm-agent` in the agent table, direct execution/usage snippet, and x-agent checks list.\n    16→- [ ] 15. Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if any implementation changed documented files, patterns, or schema.\n    17→- [ ] 16. All acceptance criteria pass — run `ralph validate work` and confirm PASS.\n    18→\n    19→## Architecture Review\n    20→\n    21→### System Design and Component Boundaries\n    22→`helm-agent` should be a domain-specific command wrapper that sits in the same agent runtime model as existing runners:\n    23→- `skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh` owns command parsing, chart discovery, per-chart command execution, and output rendering.\n    24→- `lib/x-agent-common.sh` owns reusable mechanics: output framing, timing, trap/cleanup, lock, fail-fast guard, and requirement checks.\n    25→- `.ralph/specs/06-helm-agent.md` defines FR-level behavior and required scenarios.\n    26→- `install.sh` and `README.md` are registration/presentation boundaries.\n    27→- `tests/helm-agent` drives deterministic validation via `tests/run-scenarios.sh`.\n    28→\n    29→The data path is file-system local and command-driven; no network/API calls are required in script behavior.\n    30→\n    31→### Dependency Graph and Coupling Concerns\n    32→- Direct runtime dependency: `helm` binary in PATH.\n    33→- Filesystem dependency: chart discovery relies on `Chart.yaml` existence and relative parent directories.\n    34→- Tooling dependency in execution environment: `tests/run-scenarios.sh` and `shellcheck`.\n    35→- Cross-module coupling points:\n    36→  - install path assumptions in `install.sh` (`skills/<name>/SKILL.md`, `skills/<name>/scripts/<name>-agent.sh`).\n    37→  - shared lib location contract `../../../lib`.\n    38→  - SKILL allowed-tools contract used by skill runner policies.\n    39→\n    40→Risk focus: brittle path assumptions (relative paths, discovery roots, and CHANGED_FILES expansion). Keep to existing convention of space-delimited CHANGED_FILES entries and explicit filtering logic to avoid regressions.\n    41→\n    42→### Data Flow and Bottlenecks\n    43→1. Script invoked from fixture/project directory.\n    44→2. Parse help flags and command.\n    45→3. Validate helm tool.\n    46→4. Initialize `OUTDIR` and lock via common lib.\n    47→5. Resolve chart target list.\n    48→6. Execute one or more steps against each target, writing step logs.\n    49→7. Aggregate step outcomes into `overall_ok`, emit `Overall`.\n    50→\n    51→Bottlenecks:\n    52→- `find . -name Chart.yaml` in large repos can be O(n).\n    53→- `helm lint`/`helm template` runtime scales with chart count and template size.\n    54→- CHANGED_FILES-driven execution can reduce runtime when scope is narrow.\n    55→\n    56→### Scaling Characteristics and Single Points of Failure\n    57→- Single-tenant lock (`setup_lock`) avoids concurrent overlapping runs per agent name.\n    58→- Without CHANGED_FILES scoping, full-tree discovery and linting can be expensive on large monorepos.\n    59→- Critical failure surfaces:\n    60→  - invalid `CHART_DIR` path,\n    61→  - no chart roots found,\n    62→  - malformed chart files causing command exit >0.\n    63→\n    64→### Security Architecture\n    65→- Threat surface is local filesystem path inputs (`CHART_DIR`, `CHANGED_FILES`).\n    66→- Security posture should remain non-networked and deterministic:\n    67→  - run only trusted local `helm` binary\n    68→  - quote paths when invoking commands (arrays when possible)\n    69→  - limit globbing/splitting assumptions to conventional conventions (already repo-wide).\n    70→\n    71→### Key Architectural Options\n    72→\n    73→Decision A: Chart root discovery strategy\n    74→- Option 1: Always scan entire repository for `Chart.yaml` and then apply CHANGED_FILES filtering.\n    75→  - Effort: low.\n    76→  - Risk: unnecessary scan and noisy behavior in huge trees.\n    77→  - Impact: easy to implement but less efficient.\n    78→- Option 2: If CHANGED_FILES is set, resolve only parent chart dirs first; else scan.\n    79→  - Effort: low.\n    80→  - Risk: missed chart when changed files are from untracked/deleted paths (acceptable when using best effort).\n    81→  - Impact: faster by default in incremental mode, matches FR intent.\n    82→- Option 3: Build and cache chart-index database.\n    83→  - Effort: high, requires invalidation.\n    84→  - Risk: stale cache complexity.\n    85→  - Impact: over-engineered for current scope.\n    86→\n    87→Chosen: Option 2 (explicit override > changed-file parents > repo scan).\n    88→\n    89→Decision B: Skip behavior when no charts discovered\n    90→- Option 1: Return FAIL with explicit instruction.\n    91→  - Risk: noisy in non-Helm repos; violates expected behavior pattern.\n    92→- Option 2: Return SKIP with explicit reason.\n    93→  - Risk: less strict visibility but less false failure.\n    94→\n    95→Chosen: SKIP with explicit reasons (`SKIP all steps: no chart`) to maintain consistency with existing agents.\n    96→\n    97→Decision C: Per-chart loop execution order\n    98→- Option 1: Process chart roots as discovered, run lint/template per chart immediately.\n    99→  - Effort: low.\n   100→  - Impact: direct and debuggable output.\n   101→- Option 2: Run all lint first across charts, then all template runs.\n   102→  - Effort: low but requires command batching.\n   103→  - Impact: less local context on first failure in per-chart diagnostics.\n   104→\n   105→Chosen: sequential per chart per step for better locality and actionable logs.\n   106→\n   107→## Code Quality Planning\n   108→\n   109→### Organization and Module Structure\n   110→- Keep `helm-agent.sh` under ~200 domain lines; avoid duplicating shared lib patterns.\n   111→- Suggested function boundaries:\n   112→  - `usage()`\n   113→  - `collect_chart_targets()`\n   114→  - `run_lint_one_chart()` and `run_template_one_chart()`\n   115→  - `run_lint()` and `run_template()` (iterate chart list)\n   116→  - `main()`\n   117→- Keep CHART_DIR resolution and CHANGED_FILES parsing in dedicated helpers to isolate complexity.\n   118→\n   119→### DRY Opportunities\n   120→- Reuse `step`, `print_result`, `fmt_elapsed`, `setup_outdir`, `setup_lock`, `print_overall`, `need`, and `should_continue` from shared library.\n   121→- Centralize path normalization and dedupe behavior in one helper so both lint/template share the same chart list.\n   122→- Centralize skip messaging constants for consistent user-facing wording.\n   123→\n   124→### Explicit Error Handling (all edge cases)\n   125→- Missing required tool (`helm`) => `need helm` exits 2.\n   126→- `--help` path: must execute without `helm`.\n   127→- Unknown command => usage + exit 2.\n   128→- Empty `CHART_DIR` or non-existent path => `SKIP` or `FAIL` consistently; plan says choose `SKIP` when no discoverable chart root.\n   129→- `CHANGED_FILES` set with no matching chart-related files => skip decision with reason.\n   130→- Duplicate CHANGED file roots => dedupe once before running.\n   131→- `helm lint` failure: emit truncated diagnostics + fail hint; preserve full log.\n   132→- `helm template` success: discard rendered output; still emit PASS from per-chart step.\n   133→- `helm template` failure: emit failure context + fix hint.\n   134→- Chart directory with unreadable files/permission issues: FAIL with command output preserved for troubleshooting.\n   135→- `KEEP_DIR=1` or failing exit: logs retained; success defaults to cleanup.\n   136→\n   137→### Technical Debt Prevention\n   138→- Avoid clever shell parsing or regex-heavy path logic that breaks on edge filenames.\n   139→- Keep `CHANGED_FILES` semantics explicit and deterministic.\n   140→- Keep fix-hints stable, exact, and short.\n   141→- Use small helper for chart dedupe to avoid divergence as helm, kube, docker agents are added.\n   142→\n   143→### Engineering Level\n   144→Aim for “engineered enough”: deterministic, explicit branch handling, no premature generalization into a full filesystem graph resolver abstraction.\n   145→\n   146→## Test Strategy\n   147→\n   148→### Coverage Model\n   149→- Unit-like validation (functional, via scripted fixtures): chart resolver outcomes for\n   150→  - explicit `CHART_DIR`\n   151→  - CHANGED_FILES-derived chart(s)\n   152→  - repo-wide fallback discovery\n   153→  - no chart cases\n   154→- Integration behavior:\n   155→  - `tests/run-scenarios.sh helm-agent` clean/issues\n   156→  - `shellcheck --severity=warning`\n   157→- End-to-end acceptance:\n   158→  - `ralph validate work` and all impacted tests.\n   159→\n   160→### Edge Cases + Corresponding Tests\n   161→1. Clean chart passes (`EXPECT_EXIT=0`, `RUN_ARGS=all`).\n   162→2. Broken chart fails (`EXPECT_EXIT=1`).\n   163→3. No chart in fixture -> skip all with explicit reason.\n   164→4. `CHART_DIR` explicitly set to valid chart path.\n   165→5. `CHART_DIR` set to invalid path.\n   166→6. `CHANGED_FILES` points at `.yaml/.yml/.tpl/Chart.yaml/values.yaml` in one chart -> scoped to that chart.\n   167→7. `CHANGED_FILES` contains only non-chart files -> skip (or skip-all behavior).\n   168→8. `CHANGED_FILES` references files across multiple charts -> both charts processed.\n   169→9. Duplicate CHANGED file entries -> single invocation per chart.\n   170→\n   171→### Failure Modes and Error Paths\n   172→- `helm` missing.\n   173→- `helm lint` returns non-zero with syntax/templating errors.\n   174→- `helm template` fails due unresolved values.\n   175→- `CHART_DIR` resolution yields path without `Chart.yaml`.\n   176→- `FAIL_FAST=1` stops after first failing chart/step.\n   177→\n   178→### Assertion Strength\n   179→- Assert exact exit codes (`EXPECT_EXIT`).\n   180→- Assert presence of: `Step:`, `Result: PASS|FAIL|SKIP`, `Fix:` for FAIL.\n   181→- Assert SKIP reasons are explicit and stable.\n   182→- Verify `Overall:` and `Logs:` appear.\n   183→- Confirm `All` command executes both steps unless toggles are disabled.\n   184→\n   185→## Performance Considerations\n   186→\n   187→- No DB access; all work is local file system + subprocess calls.\n   188→- Dominant costs are `find` and Helm CLI execution; avoid repeated discovery by resolving chart list once.\n   189→- Memory usage is bounded to per-step log strings and small path lists.\n   190→- No long-lived caches needed in first pass; optional future cache could track `Chart.yaml` paths for unchanged repos.\n   191→- Use `find` only when CHANGED_FILES is absent to avoid extra scans.\n   192→\n   193→## Step-by-Step Implementation Plan\n   194→\n   195→1. What: Align implementation baseline.\n   196→   Why: prevents spec drift and mismatched style.\n   197→   How: Cross-check spec 06, shared-lib contract, add quick callouts for FR mapping.\n   198→   Edge cases: spec mismatch vs existing implementation; stale patterns from gha review.\n   199→   Tests: no code tests; planning trace.\n   200→   Risks: incorrect acceptance interpretation, especially SKIP wording.\n   201→\n   202→2. What: Create `skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh` scaffold.\n   203→   Why: entrypoint and shebang contract for all agents.\n   204→   How: add header, comments, script path variables, and source shared lib.\n   205→   Edge cases: keep source path `../../../lib` correct for install modes.\n   206→   Tests: `bash -n` equivalent behavior by invocation, `--help` in non-Helm dir should still show usage.\n   207→   Risks: wrong path or missing source leading to command failures.\n   208→\n   209→3. What: Add CLI handling and tool validation order.\n   210→   Why: meets FR-5 and prevents accidental exits for `--help`.\n   211→   How: parse `help` flags before `need helm`; parse `--fail-fast`; command parser for `lint`, `template`, `all`.\n   212→   Edge cases: unknown command should output usage and exit 2.\n   213→   Tests: command smoke checks and expected return codes in scenario.\n   214→   Risks: accidental tool check before help or command parsing.\n   215→\n   216→4. What: Add universal knob definitions and shared runtime integration.\n   217→   Why: FR-2 and output consistency.\n   218→   How: set `RUN_LINT`, `RUN_TEMPLATE`; rely on shared defaults for universal knobs.\n   219→   Edge cases: CHANGED_FILES not set vs set empty.\n   220→   Tests: `RUN_LINT=0`, `RUN_TEMPLATE=0`, `FAIL_FAST` path checks.\n   221→   Risks: local override accidentally shadowing shared `MAX_LINES` semantics.\n   222→\n   223→5. What: Implement `collect_chart_targets()`.\n   224→   Why: foundation for all behavior and scope correctness.\n   225→   How: precedence logic:\n   226→      - if `CHART_DIR` non-empty and directory exists, verify/resolve chart candidate.\n   227→      - else parse `CHANGED_FILES` for chart-related extensions and resolve parent `Chart.yaml` files.\n   228→      - else scan for `Chart.yaml` recursively.\n   229→      - dedupe and preserve deterministic order.\n   230→      - emit skip reason when none found.\n   231→   Edge cases: duplicate paths, nonexistent files, nested chart dirs, subchart files.\n   232→   Tests: dedicated scenarios for each branch.\n   233→   Risks: parent traversal misses chart root when `.tpl` file appears in umbrella/subchart boundaries.\n   234→\n   235→6. What: Implement `run_lint` over resolved chart list.\n   236→   Why: satisfies FR-6 and lint acceptance.\n   237→   How: loop charts; for each run `helm lint <chart>` to `<OUTDIR>/lint.<idx>.log`; aggregate exit code; call `print_result` style output and custom failure context.\n   238→   Edge cases: command writes to stdout+stderr, partial failures, one bad chart.\n   239→   Tests: `issues` fixture and multi-chart negative fixture (optional).\n   240→   Risks: hidden failures if one chart succeeds and another fails are not surfaced due aggregator bug.\n   241→\n   242→7. What: Implement `run_template` over resolved chart list.\n   243→   Why: FR-9 and template rendering validation.\n   244→   How: loop charts; run `helm template <chart>` with output redirected to `/dev/null` while preserving logs; treat non-zero as FAIL.\n   245→   Edge cases: large rendered output; command should not blow memory.\n   246→   Tests: issue fixture with bad template expression.\n   247→   Risks: output redirection accidentally hides diagnostics (guard by log file).\n   248→\n   249→8. What: Implement `all` orchestration and per-step toggles.\n   250→   Why: aligns with command contract and run ordering.\n   251→   How: in `all`, evaluate `RUN_LINT` then `RUN_TEMPLATE` using `should_continue`.\n   252→   Edge cases: only one step enabled, fail-fast set, explicit `RUN_*` off toggles.\n   253→   Tests: `RUN_LINT=0` and `RUN_TEMPLATE=0` scenarios.\n   254→   Risks: fail-fast bypass from mis-scoped `overall_ok` handling.\n   255→\n   256→9. What: Add deterministic skip and reason strings.\n   257→   Why: user-visible contract and reviewability.\n   258→   How: emit specific messages:\n   259→      - no chart root discovered via all methods,\n   260→      - CHANGED_FILES set but no chart-related files,\n   261→      - explicit `CHART_DIR` invalid.\n   262→   Edge cases: avoid wording collisions with prior gha-agent review to keep consistency.\n   263→   Tests: skip scenarios assert matching result text.\n   264→   Risks: inconsistent strings causing brittle manual checks.\n   265→\n   266→10. What: Add `skills/helm-agent/SKILL.md`.\n   267→    Why: FR-11 and agent invocation metadata.\n   268→    How: include triggers, allowed-tools list for `RUN_*`, `CHART_DIR`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, `MAX_LINES`, `KEEP_DIR`, `FAIL_FAST`, `CHANGED_FILES`.\n   269→    Edge cases: missing TMPDIR_ROOT in allowed-tools if policy expects it.\n   270→    Tests: manual review + invocation compatibility.\n   271→    Risks: blocked invocation in skill-driven runs.\n   272→\n   273→11. What: Author `tests/helm-agent/clean/` fixture.\n   274→    Why: validates happy path and chart discovery baseline.\n   275→    How: add minimal chart (`Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `templates/configmap.yaml`) and required `scenario.env`.\n   276→    Edge cases: ensure `values.yaml` keys used by template exist.\n   277→    Tests: scenario expects exit 0.\n   278→    Risks: missing value keys causing false fails in template checks.\n   279→\n   280→12. What: Author `tests/helm-agent/issues/` fixture.\n   281→    Why: validates deterministic failure for lint/template checks.\n   282→    How: craft deterministic failure in template (e.g., `.Values.missing | required \"msg\"` with missing value in `values.yaml`), keep failure signal stable across helm versions.\n   283→    Edge cases: avoid behavior that varies by lint profile/config.\n   284→    Tests: scenario expects exit 1.\n   285→    Risks: false-fail if failure pattern depends on chart engine defaults.\n   286→\n   287→13. What: Add explicit edge scenario coverage for scope and skip.\n   288→    Why: direct gap closure from previous feedback and spec-test strategy.\n   289→    How: add scenario files for:\n   290→      - `CHANGED_FILES` pointing to one chart file (expect scoped pass/fail as appropriate),\n   291→      - `CHANGED_FILES` only non-chart files (expect skip),\n   292→      - explicit `CHART_DIR` invalid/missing (expect skip/fail as defined).\n   293→    Edge cases: ensures no-match and override precedence are exercised.\n   294→    Tests: run `tests/run-scenarios.sh helm-agent` with filtered and full path checks.\n   295→    Risks: over-expanding fixture set vs simplicity; keep fixtures minimal.\n   296→\n   297→14. What: Update `install.sh` and README.\n   298→    Why: FR-13 discovery and usability requirement.\n   299→    How: add helm-agent to `SKILLS`, optional tool check behavior, install snippet line, table row, and usage examples.\n   300→    Edge cases: maintain ordering and existing wording consistency.\n   301→    Tests: basic grep checks + scenario run unaffected for unrelated agents.\n   302→    Risks: merge conflicts in shared docs if other agents already edited concurrently.\n   303→\n   304→15. What: Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if needed.\n   305→    Why: keep orientation docs current for next plan iterations.\n   306→    How: record helm additions, fixture directories, and any updated patterns (chart scoping, skip-first strategy).\n   307→    Edge cases: stale notes around key file inventory.\n   308→    Risks: downstream work agents duplicating discovery effort.\n   309→\n   310→16. What: Validate completion.\n   311→    Why: required acceptance gating.\n   312→    How: run `ralph validate plan`, then execute checklist-driven implementation plus `ralph validate work`.\n   313→    Edge cases: ensure both check commands pass in this environment.\n   314→    Risks: validation false negatives due missing tooling.\n   315→\n   316→## Decision Log\n   317→\n   318→- Decision 1: Make `CHANGED_FILES` branch subordinate to explicit `CHART_DIR` and fallback scan.\n   319→  - Options considered: (a) ignore `CHANGED_FILES` entirely for discovery; (b) always apply `CHANGED_FILES` first; (c) explicit override priority chain.\n   320→  - Chosen: explicit override first, then scoped discovery, then global discovery.\n   321→  - Impact: matches FR and avoids surprising runs when the user intentionally sets `CHART_DIR`.\n   322→\n   323→- Decision 2: Keep `CHART_DIR`/no-chart conditions as `SKIP` rather than `FAIL`.\n   324→  - Options considered: fail hard on missing charts vs skip with context.\n   325→  - Chosen: SKIP with explicit reason (consistent with non-applicable tool behavior in existing agents).\n   326→  - Impact: less brittle CI when running in mixed-repo environments.\n   327→\n   328→- Decision 3: Use per-chart sequential execution with failure aggregation.\n   329→  - Options considered: aggregate chart list and batch command once vs iterative per-chart loops.\n   330→  - Chosen: iterative per-chart with deterministic logs.\n   331→  - Impact: clearer logs and easier pinpointing when multiple charts exist.\n   332→\n   333→## Edge Cases and Risks\n   334→\n   335→- `CHART_DIR` explicitly set and points to a non-existent or non-chart directory.\n   336→- `CHANGED_FILES` contains entries with spaces (shared convention assumes whitespace-split; document and test skip/acceptance).\n   337→- `CHANGED_FILES` contains duplicates and nested chart files; ensure unique chart roots.\n   338→- Multiple charts affected in one run; ensure all are processed and aggregate outcome is correct.\n   339→- No `Chart.yaml` under cwd; both commands should skip with explicit reason and clean exit.\n   340→- Chart templates with invalid but non-fatal-looking syntax in helm lint mode; ensure template command still catches render failures.\n   341→- `helm` missing in environment when scenarios declare it absent; should skip via `REQUIRED_TOOLS` rather than script execution failures.\n   342→- Optional `FAIL_FAST` should stop orchestration after first failed step.\n   343→- Long-running charts should not fill stdout in memory; logs written to disk.\n   344→- `TEMPLATE` command output must be discarded (except log) to avoid large-memory and huge fixture logs.\n   345→- `install.sh` remote install path integrity and SKILL snippet auto-patching for `CHART_DIR` path hints.\n   346→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be0e30e7-8817-4b77-ad57-f2dbd38ea5b9","uuid":"296dcdf2-3f6b-4ed1-9681-50caf7a837e3","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/work-plan.txt","content":"## Implementation Checklist\n- [ ] 1. Confirm `AGENTS.md`, `.ralph/task.md`, `.ralph/specs/06-helm-agent.md`, `docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`, and `docs/agents/definition-of-done.md` constraints against the current repo state.\n- [ ] 2. Create `skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh` with Bash 3.2-safe header and explicit usage of `set -euo pipefail`.\n- [ ] 3. Source `lib/x-agent-common.sh` via `SCRIPT_DIR/../../../lib` and rely on shared helpers for `step`, timing, output, trap, lock, fail-fast, and `need()`.\n- [ ] 4. Implement required knobs and defaults: `RUN_LINT`, `RUN_TEMPLATE`, `CHART_DIR`, and universal knobs (`KEEP_DIR`, `MAX_LINES`, `FAIL_FAST`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, `CHANGED_FILES`).\n- [ ] 5. Add `--help`/`help`/`-h` early dispatch and required-tool validation with `need helm` in the non-help execution path.\n- [ ] 6. Implement chart detection resolver with precedence: `CHART_DIR` > `CHANGED_FILES`-derived chart roots > recursive `Chart.yaml` search.\n- [ ] 7. Implement `lint` command as `helm lint` with per-chart iteration, log capture, and strict `Fix: resolve the chart errors above, then re-run: /helm-agent lint`.\n- [ ] 8. Implement `template` command as `helm template` with per-chart iteration, output discard on success, and strict failure log reporting with `Fix: resolve the template errors above, then re-run: /helm-agent template`.\n- [ ] 9. Implement command orchestration for `lint`, `template`, `all` with `RUN_*` toggles, `FAIL_FAST` guard, and `Overall` aggregation.\n- [ ] 10. Add `skills/helm-agent/SKILL.md` with triggers and allowed-tools (including `CHART_DIR=*` and universal knobs).\n- [ ] 11. Add `tests/helm-agent/clean/` scenario fixture and `tests/helm-agent/issues/` scenario fixture with deterministic behavior and `REQUIRED_TOOLS=\"helm\"`.\n- [ ] 12. Add explicit scope/skip tests for Helm chart detection edge cases (`CHANGED_FILES` scope resolution and no `Chart.yaml` skip) using additional scenario directories.\n- [ ] 13. Update `install.sh` to register helm-agent, include optional dependency hints for helm, and include the AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet line.\n- [ ] 14. Update `README.md` with `helm-agent` in the agent table, direct execution/usage snippet, and x-agent checks list.\n- [ ] 15. Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if any implementation changed documented files, patterns, or schema.\n- [ ] 16. All acceptance criteria pass — run `ralph validate work` and confirm PASS.\n\n## Architecture Review\n\n### System Design and Component Boundaries\n`helm-agent` should be a domain-specific command wrapper that sits in the same agent runtime model as existing runners:\n- `skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh` owns command parsing, chart discovery, per-chart command execution, and output rendering.\n- `lib/x-agent-common.sh` owns reusable mechanics: output framing, timing, trap/cleanup, lock, fail-fast guard, and requirement checks.\n- `.ralph/specs/06-helm-agent.md` defines FR-level behavior and required scenarios.\n- `install.sh` and `README.md` are registration/presentation boundaries.\n- `tests/helm-agent` drives deterministic validation via `tests/run-scenarios.sh`.\n\nThe data path is file-system local and command-driven; no network/API calls are required in script behavior.\n\n### Dependency Graph and Coupling Concerns\n- Direct runtime dependency: `helm` binary in PATH.\n- Filesystem dependency: chart discovery relies on `Chart.yaml` existence and relative parent directories.\n- Tooling dependency in execution environment: `tests/run-scenarios.sh` and `shellcheck`.\n- Cross-module coupling points:\n  - install path assumptions in `install.sh` (`skills/<name>/SKILL.md`, `skills/<name>/scripts/<name>-agent.sh`).\n  - shared lib location contract `../../../lib`.\n  - SKILL allowed-tools contract used by skill runner policies.\n\nRisk focus: brittle path assumptions (relative paths, discovery roots, and CHANGED_FILES expansion). Keep to existing convention of space-delimited CHANGED_FILES entries and explicit filtering logic to avoid regressions.\n\n### Data Flow and Bottlenecks\n1. Script invoked from fixture/project directory.\n2. Parse help flags and command.\n3. Validate helm tool.\n4. Initialize `OUTDIR` and lock via common lib.\n5. Resolve chart target list.\n6. Execute one or more steps against each target, writing step logs.\n7. Aggregate step outcomes into `overall_ok`, emit `Overall`.\n\nBottlenecks:\n- `find . -name Chart.yaml` in large repos can be O(n).\n- `helm lint`/`helm template` runtime scales with chart count and template size.\n- CHANGED_FILES-driven execution can reduce runtime when scope is narrow.\n\n### Scaling Characteristics and Single Points of Failure\n- Single-tenant lock (`setup_lock`) avoids concurrent overlapping runs per agent name.\n- Without CHANGED_FILES scoping, full-tree discovery and linting can be expensive on large monorepos.\n- Critical failure surfaces:\n  - invalid `CHART_DIR` path,\n  - no chart roots found,\n  - malformed chart files causing command exit >0.\n\n### Security Architecture\n- Threat surface is local filesystem path inputs (`CHART_DIR`, `CHANGED_FILES`).\n- Security posture should remain non-networked and deterministic:\n  - run only trusted local `helm` binary\n  - quote paths when invoking commands (arrays when possible)\n  - limit globbing/splitting assumptions to conventional conventions (already repo-wide).\n\n### Key Architectural Options\n\nDecision A: Chart root discovery strategy\n- Option 1: Always scan entire repository for `Chart.yaml` and then apply CHANGED_FILES filtering.\n  - Effort: low.\n  - Risk: unnecessary scan and noisy behavior in huge trees.\n  - Impact: easy to implement but less efficient.\n- Option 2: If CHANGED_FILES is set, resolve only parent chart dirs first; else scan.\n  - Effort: low.\n  - Risk: missed chart when changed files are from untracked/deleted paths (acceptable when using best effort).\n  - Impact: faster by default in incremental mode, matches FR intent.\n- Option 3: Build and cache chart-index database.\n  - Effort: high, requires invalidation.\n  - Risk: stale cache complexity.\n  - Impact: over-engineered for current scope.\n\nChosen: Option 2 (explicit override > changed-file parents > repo scan).\n\nDecision B: Skip behavior when no charts discovered\n- Option 1: Return FAIL with explicit instruction.\n  - Risk: noisy in non-Helm repos; violates expected behavior pattern.\n- Option 2: Return SKIP with explicit reason.\n  - Risk: less strict visibility but less false failure.\n\nChosen: SKIP with explicit reasons (`SKIP all steps: no chart`) to maintain consistency with existing agents.\n\nDecision C: Per-chart loop execution order\n- Option 1: Process chart roots as discovered, run lint/template per chart immediately.\n  - Effort: low.\n  - Impact: direct and debuggable output.\n- Option 2: Run all lint first across charts, then all template runs.\n  - Effort: low but requires command batching.\n  - Impact: less local context on first failure in per-chart diagnostics.\n\nChosen: sequential per chart per step for better locality and actionable logs.\n\n## Code Quality Planning\n\n### Organization and Module Structure\n- Keep `helm-agent.sh` under ~200 domain lines; avoid duplicating shared lib patterns.\n- Suggested function boundaries:\n  - `usage()`\n  - `collect_chart_targets()`\n  - `run_lint_one_chart()` and `run_template_one_chart()`\n  - `run_lint()` and `run_template()` (iterate chart list)\n  - `main()`\n- Keep CHART_DIR resolution and CHANGED_FILES parsing in dedicated helpers to isolate complexity.\n\n### DRY Opportunities\n- Reuse `step`, `print_result`, `fmt_elapsed`, `setup_outdir`, `setup_lock`, `print_overall`, `need`, and `should_continue` from shared library.\n- Centralize path normalization and dedupe behavior in one helper so both lint/template share the same chart list.\n- Centralize skip messaging constants for consistent user-facing wording.\n\n### Explicit Error Handling (all edge cases)\n- Missing required tool (`helm`) => `need helm` exits 2.\n- `--help` path: must execute without `helm`.\n- Unknown command => usage + exit 2.\n- Empty `CHART_DIR` or non-existent path => `SKIP` or `FAIL` consistently; plan says choose `SKIP` when no discoverable chart root.\n- `CHANGED_FILES` set with no matching chart-related files => skip decision with reason.\n- Duplicate CHANGED file roots => dedupe once before running.\n- `helm lint` failure: emit truncated diagnostics + fail hint; preserve full log.\n- `helm template` success: discard rendered output; still emit PASS from per-chart step.\n- `helm template` failure: emit failure context + fix hint.\n- Chart directory with unreadable files/permission issues: FAIL with command output preserved for troubleshooting.\n- `KEEP_DIR=1` or failing exit: logs retained; success defaults to cleanup.\n\n### Technical Debt Prevention\n- Avoid clever shell parsing or regex-heavy path logic that breaks on edge filenames.\n- Keep `CHANGED_FILES` semantics explicit and deterministic.\n- Keep fix-hints stable, exact, and short.\n- Use small helper for chart dedupe to avoid divergence as helm, kube, docker agents are added.\n\n### Engineering Level\nAim for “engineered enough”: deterministic, explicit branch handling, no premature generalization into a full filesystem graph resolver abstraction.\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Coverage Model\n- Unit-like validation (functional, via scripted fixtures): chart resolver outcomes for\n  - explicit `CHART_DIR`\n  - CHANGED_FILES-derived chart(s)\n  - repo-wide fallback discovery\n  - no chart cases\n- Integration behavior:\n  - `tests/run-scenarios.sh helm-agent` clean/issues\n  - `shellcheck --severity=warning`\n- End-to-end acceptance:\n  - `ralph validate work` and all impacted tests.\n\n### Edge Cases + Corresponding Tests\n1. Clean chart passes (`EXPECT_EXIT=0`, `RUN_ARGS=all`).\n2. Broken chart fails (`EXPECT_EXIT=1`).\n3. No chart in fixture -> skip all with explicit reason.\n4. `CHART_DIR` explicitly set to valid chart path.\n5. `CHART_DIR` set to invalid path.\n6. `CHANGED_FILES` points at `.yaml/.yml/.tpl/Chart.yaml/values.yaml` in one chart -> scoped to that chart.\n7. `CHANGED_FILES` contains only non-chart files -> skip (or skip-all behavior).\n8. `CHANGED_FILES` references files across multiple charts -> both charts processed.\n9. Duplicate CHANGED file entries -> single invocation per chart.\n\n### Failure Modes and Error Paths\n- `helm` missing.\n- `helm lint` returns non-zero with syntax/templating errors.\n- `helm template` fails due unresolved values.\n- `CHART_DIR` resolution yields path without `Chart.yaml`.\n- `FAIL_FAST=1` stops after first failing chart/step.\n\n### Assertion Strength\n- Assert exact exit codes (`EXPECT_EXIT`).\n- Assert presence of: `Step:`, `Result: PASS|FAIL|SKIP`, `Fix:` for FAIL.\n- Assert SKIP reasons are explicit and stable.\n- Verify `Overall:` and `Logs:` appear.\n- Confirm `All` command executes both steps unless toggles are disabled.\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n- No DB access; all work is local file system + subprocess calls.\n- Dominant costs are `find` and Helm CLI execution; avoid repeated discovery by resolving chart list once.\n- Memory usage is bounded to per-step log strings and small path lists.\n- No long-lived caches needed in first pass; optional future cache could track `Chart.yaml` paths for unchanged repos.\n- Use `find` only when CHANGED_FILES is absent to avoid extra scans.\n\n## Step-by-Step Implementation Plan\n\n1. What: Align implementation baseline.\n   Why: prevents spec drift and mismatched style.\n   How: Cross-check spec 06, shared-lib contract, add quick callouts for FR mapping.\n   Edge cases: spec mismatch vs existing implementation; stale patterns from gha review.\n   Tests: no code tests; planning trace.\n   Risks: incorrect acceptance interpretation, especially SKIP wording.\n\n2. What: Create `skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh` scaffold.\n   Why: entrypoint and shebang contract for all agents.\n   How: add header, comments, script path variables, and source shared lib.\n   Edge cases: keep source path `../../../lib` correct for install modes.\n   Tests: `bash -n` equivalent behavior by invocation, `--help` in non-Helm dir should still show usage.\n   Risks: wrong path or missing source leading to command failures.\n\n3. What: Add CLI handling and tool validation order.\n   Why: meets FR-5 and prevents accidental exits for `--help`.\n   How: parse `help` flags before `need helm`; parse `--fail-fast`; command parser for `lint`, `template`, `all`.\n   Edge cases: unknown command should output usage and exit 2.\n   Tests: command smoke checks and expected return codes in scenario.\n   Risks: accidental tool check before help or command parsing.\n\n4. What: Add universal knob definitions and shared runtime integration.\n   Why: FR-2 and output consistency.\n   How: set `RUN_LINT`, `RUN_TEMPLATE`; rely on shared defaults for universal knobs.\n   Edge cases: CHANGED_FILES not set vs set empty.\n   Tests: `RUN_LINT=0`, `RUN_TEMPLATE=0`, `FAIL_FAST` path checks.\n   Risks: local override accidentally shadowing shared `MAX_LINES` semantics.\n\n5. What: Implement `collect_chart_targets()`.\n   Why: foundation for all behavior and scope correctness.\n   How: precedence logic:\n      - if `CHART_DIR` non-empty and directory exists, verify/resolve chart candidate.\n      - else parse `CHANGED_FILES` for chart-related extensions and resolve parent `Chart.yaml` files.\n      - else scan for `Chart.yaml` recursively.\n      - dedupe and preserve deterministic order.\n      - emit skip reason when none found.\n   Edge cases: duplicate paths, nonexistent files, nested chart dirs, subchart files.\n   Tests: dedicated scenarios for each branch.\n   Risks: parent traversal misses chart root when `.tpl` file appears in umbrella/subchart boundaries.\n\n6. What: Implement `run_lint` over resolved chart list.\n   Why: satisfies FR-6 and lint acceptance.\n   How: loop charts; for each run `helm lint <chart>` to `<OUTDIR>/lint.<idx>.log`; aggregate exit code; call `print_result` style output and custom failure context.\n   Edge cases: command writes to stdout+stderr, partial failures, one bad chart.\n   Tests: `issues` fixture and multi-chart negative fixture (optional).\n   Risks: hidden failures if one chart succeeds and another fails are not surfaced due aggregator bug.\n\n7. What: Implement `run_template` over resolved chart list.\n   Why: FR-9 and template rendering validation.\n   How: loop charts; run `helm template <chart>` with output redirected to `/dev/null` while preserving logs; treat non-zero as FAIL.\n   Edge cases: large rendered output; command should not blow memory.\n   Tests: issue fixture with bad template expression.\n   Risks: output redirection accidentally hides diagnostics (guard by log file).\n\n8. What: Implement `all` orchestration and per-step toggles.\n   Why: aligns with command contract and run ordering.\n   How: in `all`, evaluate `RUN_LINT` then `RUN_TEMPLATE` using `should_continue`.\n   Edge cases: only one step enabled, fail-fast set, explicit `RUN_*` off toggles.\n   Tests: `RUN_LINT=0` and `RUN_TEMPLATE=0` scenarios.\n   Risks: fail-fast bypass from mis-scoped `overall_ok` handling.\n\n9. What: Add deterministic skip and reason strings.\n   Why: user-visible contract and reviewability.\n   How: emit specific messages:\n      - no chart root discovered via all methods,\n      - CHANGED_FILES set but no chart-related files,\n      - explicit `CHART_DIR` invalid.\n   Edge cases: avoid wording collisions with prior gha-agent review to keep consistency.\n   Tests: skip scenarios assert matching result text.\n   Risks: inconsistent strings causing brittle manual checks.\n\n10. What: Add `skills/helm-agent/SKILL.md`.\n    Why: FR-11 and agent invocation metadata.\n    How: include triggers, allowed-tools list for `RUN_*`, `CHART_DIR`, `TMPDIR_ROOT`, `MAX_LINES`, `KEEP_DIR`, `FAIL_FAST`, `CHANGED_FILES`.\n    Edge cases: missing TMPDIR_ROOT in allowed-tools if policy expects it.\n    Tests: manual review + invocation compatibility.\n    Risks: blocked invocation in skill-driven runs.\n\n11. What: Author `tests/helm-agent/clean/` fixture.\n    Why: validates happy path and chart discovery baseline.\n    How: add minimal chart (`Chart.yaml`, `values.yaml`, `templates/configmap.yaml`) and required `scenario.env`.\n    Edge cases: ensure `values.yaml` keys used by template exist.\n    Tests: scenario expects exit 0.\n    Risks: missing value keys causing false fails in template checks.\n\n12. What: Author `tests/helm-agent/issues/` fixture.\n    Why: validates deterministic failure for lint/template checks.\n    How: craft deterministic failure in template (e.g., `.Values.missing | required \"msg\"` with missing value in `values.yaml`), keep failure signal stable across helm versions.\n    Edge cases: avoid behavior that varies by lint profile/config.\n    Tests: scenario expects exit 1.\n    Risks: false-fail if failure pattern depends on chart engine defaults.\n\n13. What: Add explicit edge scenario coverage for scope and skip.\n    Why: direct gap closure from previous feedback and spec-test strategy.\n    How: add scenario files for:\n      - `CHANGED_FILES` pointing to one chart file (expect scoped pass/fail as appropriate),\n      - `CHANGED_FILES` only non-chart files (expect skip),\n      - explicit `CHART_DIR` invalid/missing (expect skip/fail as defined).\n    Edge cases: ensures no-match and override precedence are exercised.\n    Tests: run `tests/run-scenarios.sh helm-agent` with filtered and full path checks.\n    Risks: over-expanding fixture set vs simplicity; keep fixtures minimal.\n\n14. What: Update `install.sh` and README.\n    Why: FR-13 discovery and usability requirement.\n    How: add helm-agent to `SKILLS`, optional tool check behavior, install snippet line, table row, and usage examples.\n    Edge cases: maintain ordering and existing wording consistency.\n    Tests: basic grep checks + scenario run unaffected for unrelated agents.\n    Risks: merge conflicts in shared docs if other agents already edited concurrently.\n\n15. What: Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if needed.\n    Why: keep orientation docs current for next plan iterations.\n    How: record helm additions, fixture directories, and any updated patterns (chart scoping, skip-first strategy).\n    Edge cases: stale notes around key file inventory.\n    Risks: downstream work agents duplicating discovery effort.\n\n16. What: Validate completion.\n    Why: required acceptance gating.\n    How: run `ralph validate plan`, then execute checklist-driven implementation plus `ralph validate work`.\n    Edge cases: ensure both check commands pass in this environment.\n    Risks: validation false negatives due missing tooling.\n\n## Decision Log\n\n- Decision 1: Make `CHANGED_FILES` branch subordinate to explicit `CHART_DIR` and fallback scan.\n  - Options considered: (a) ignore `CHANGED_FILES` entirely for discovery; (b) always apply `CHANGED_FILES` first; (c) explicit override priority chain.\n  - Chosen: explicit override first, then scoped discovery, then global discovery.\n  - Impact: matches FR and avoids surprising runs when the user intentionally sets `CHART_DIR`.\n\n- Decision 2: Keep `CHART_DIR`/no-chart conditions as `SKIP` rather than `FAIL`.\n  - Options considered: fail hard on missing charts vs skip with context.\n  - Chosen: SKIP with explicit reason (consistent with non-applicable tool behavior in existing agents).\n  - Impact: less brittle CI when running in mixed-repo environments.\n\n- Decision 3: Use per-chart sequential execution with failure aggregation.\n  - Options considered: aggregate chart list and batch command once vs iterative per-chart loops.\n  - Chosen: iterative per-chart with deterministic logs.\n  - Impact: clearer logs and easier pinpointing when multiple charts exist.\n\n## Edge Cases and Risks\n\n- `CHART_DIR` explicitly set and points to a non-existent or non-chart directory.\n- `CHANGED_FILES` contains entries with spaces (shared convention assumes whitespace-split; document and test skip/acceptance).\n- `CHANGED_FILES` contains duplicates and nested chart files; ensure unique chart roots.\n- Multiple charts affected in one run; ensure all are processed and aggregate outcome is correct.\n- No `Chart.yaml` under cwd; both commands should skip with explicit reason and clean exit.\n- Chart templates with invalid but non-fatal-looking syntax in helm lint mode; ensure template command still catches render failures.\n- `helm` missing in environment when scenarios declare it absent; should skip via `REQUIRED_TOOLS` rather than script execution failures.\n- Optional `FAIL_FAST` should stop orchestration after first failed step.\n- Long-running charts should not fill stdout in memory; logs written to disk.\n- `TEMPLATE` command output must be discarded (except log) to avoid large-memory and huge fixture logs.\n- `install.sh` remote install path integrity and SKILL snippet auto-patching for `CHART_DIR` path hints.\n","numLines":346,"startLine":1,"totalLines":346}}}
