{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SV8AyumxsyPMjkTJQWdvr2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: gha-agent\n     3→description: |\n     4→  Run gha-agent.sh — a lean GitHub Actions workflow linter that produces agent-friendly output.\n     5→  Use when: running GitHub Actions workflow checks, linting workflow files, verifying workflows before committing,\n     6→  or when the user asks to run actionlint, workflow lint, or GitHub Actions checks.\n     7→  Triggers on: gha agent, github actions lint, actionlint, workflow lint, github actions checks.\n     8→context: fork\n     9→allowed-tools:\n    10→  - Bash(scripts/gha-agent.sh*)\n    11→  - Bash(RUN_*=* scripts/gha-agent.sh*)\n    12→  - Bash(MAX_LINES=* scripts/gha-agent.sh*)\n    13→  - Bash(KEEP_DIR=* scripts/gha-agent.sh*)\n    14→  - Bash(FAIL_FAST=* scripts/gha-agent.sh*)\n    15→  - Bash(CHANGED_FILES=* scripts/gha-agent.sh*)\n    16→---\n    17→\n    18→# GHA Agent\n    19→\n    20→Run the `gha-agent.sh` script for lean, structured GitHub Actions workflow linting output designed for coding agents.\n    21→\n    22→## Script Location\n    23→\n    24→```\n    25→scripts/gha-agent.sh\n    26→```\n    27→\n    28→## Usage\n    29→\n    30→### Run Full Suite (lint)\n    31→```bash\n    32→scripts/gha-agent.sh\n    33→```\n    34→\n    35→### Run Individual Steps\n    36→```bash\n    37→scripts/gha-agent.sh lint      # actionlint check only\n    38→scripts/gha-agent.sh all       # full suite (default)\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→## Environment Knobs\n    42→\n    43→| Variable | Default | Description |\n    44→|----------|---------|-------------|\n    45→| `RUN_LINT` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip lint step |\n    46→| `FAIL_FAST` | `0` | Set to `1` to stop after first failure (or use `--fail-fast`) |\n    47→| `CHANGED_FILES` | _(empty)_ | Space-separated changed file paths; scopes checks to workflow files only |\n    48→| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max output lines printed per step (unlimited in CI) |\n    49→| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n    50→\n    51→## Output Format\n    52→\n    53→- Each step prints a header (`Step: lint`)\n    54→- Results are `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `SKIP`\n    55→- On failure, output is truncated to `MAX_LINES`\n    56→- Full logs are saved to a temp directory (path printed in output)\n    57→- Overall result is printed at the end: `Overall: PASS` or `Overall: FAIL`\n    58→\n    59→## Important Notes\n    60→\n    61→- The script discovers `.yml` and `.yaml` files in `.github/workflows/`\n    62→- `CHANGED_FILES` scopes checks to only workflow files (`.yml`/`.yaml` under `.github/workflows/`)\n    63→- Reports SKIP when no `.github/workflows/` directory exists\n    64→- In CI (`CI=true`), `MAX_LINES` defaults to unlimited; locally it defaults to 40\n    65→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BEJvUovoZReNGGRcar99ZU","session_id":"be0e30e7-8817-4b77-ad57-f2dbd38ea5b9","uuid":"6d150ce9-d5af-4998-84af-5e96970df2ab"}
