{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0182MLqhTASjEnpDVi9KYYMz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## File Contents Report\n\n### 1. install.sh\nFull shell script installer for x-agent skills. Key features:\n- Supports both local and remote installation via curl\n- Interactive prompts for skill selection and install destination\n- Installs to ~/.claude/skills and ~/.codex/skills\n- Lists available skills: bash-agent, cargo-agent, gha-agent, go-agent, npm-agent, py-agent, terra-agent\n- Checks optional dependencies (shellcheck, actionlint, go, cargo, node, python3, terraform, etc.)\n- For local installs, creates symlinks; for remote installs, copies files\n- Prints AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md snippet for documentation\n\n### 2. README.md\nDocumentation for x-agent. Contents:\n- Overview: x-agent reduces token waste by providing structured pass/fail output with truncated diagnostics\n- Available agents table listing 7 agents (bash, cargo, gha, go, npm, py, terra)\n- Quick start with curl, local clone, and direct usage examples\n- Detailed usage for each agent with examples and environment variables\n- Shared environment knobs: RUN_<STEP>, MAX_LINES, KEEP_DIR\n- Output format example showing structured Step/Result/Overall format\n- Claude Code skills documentation\n\n### 3. tests/gha-agent/clean/.github/workflows/ci.yml\nClean test fixture workflow file with valid syntax:\n```yaml\nname: CI\non: [push]\njobs:\n  test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: echo \"hello\"\n```\n\n### 4. tests/gha-agent/issues/.github/workflows/bad.yml\nIssues test fixture workflow with intentional problems:\n```yaml\nname: Bad\non: [push]\njobs:\n  test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: echo ${{ github.event.inputs.name }}\n```\n(The issue: references `github.event.inputs.name` which doesn't exist in a push event)\n\n### 5. tests/gha-agent/issues/scenario.env\nTest scenario configuration:\n```\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"gha-agent issues\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=1\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"actionlint\"\n```\nSpecifies the test should fail with exit code 1 when run with actionlint tool."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7abc6c54e04a8053 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 23273\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 8771</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be0e30e7-8817-4b77-ad57-f2dbd38ea5b9","uuid":"3e088c7b-699c-4206-85fa-5f1a686cc90e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files and return their FULL contents:\n1. install.sh\n2. README.md\n3. tests/gha-agent/clean/.github/workflows/ci.yml\n4. tests/gha-agent/issues/.github/workflows/bad.yml\n5. tests/gha-agent/issues/scenario.env\n\nReturn the complete contents for each, clearly labeled.","agentId":"a7abc6c54e04a8053","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## File Contents Report\n\n### 1. install.sh\nFull shell script installer for x-agent skills. Key features:\n- Supports both local and remote installation via curl\n- Interactive prompts for skill selection and install destination\n- Installs to ~/.claude/skills and ~/.codex/skills\n- Lists available skills: bash-agent, cargo-agent, gha-agent, go-agent, npm-agent, py-agent, terra-agent\n- Checks optional dependencies (shellcheck, actionlint, go, cargo, node, python3, terraform, etc.)\n- For local installs, creates symlinks; for remote installs, copies files\n- Prints AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md snippet for documentation\n\n### 2. README.md\nDocumentation for x-agent. Contents:\n- Overview: x-agent reduces token waste by providing structured pass/fail output with truncated diagnostics\n- Available agents table listing 7 agents (bash, cargo, gha, go, npm, py, terra)\n- Quick start with curl, local clone, and direct usage examples\n- Detailed usage for each agent with examples and environment variables\n- Shared environment knobs: RUN_<STEP>, MAX_LINES, KEEP_DIR\n- Output format example showing structured Step/Result/Overall format\n- Claude Code skills documentation\n\n### 3. tests/gha-agent/clean/.github/workflows/ci.yml\nClean test fixture workflow file with valid syntax:\n```yaml\nname: CI\non: [push]\njobs:\n  test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: echo \"hello\"\n```\n\n### 4. tests/gha-agent/issues/.github/workflows/bad.yml\nIssues test fixture workflow with intentional problems:\n```yaml\nname: Bad\non: [push]\njobs:\n  test:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - run: echo ${{ github.event.inputs.name }}\n```\n(The issue: references `github.event.inputs.name` which doesn't exist in a push event)\n\n### 5. tests/gha-agent/issues/scenario.env\nTest scenario configuration:\n```\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"gha-agent issues\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=1\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"actionlint\"\n```\nSpecifies the test should fail with exit code 1 when run with actionlint tool."}],"totalDurationMs":8771,"totalTokens":23273,"totalToolUseCount":5,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9675,"cache_read_input_tokens":12981,"output_tokens":610,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9675},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
