{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RwdQCwBpCRc6LkquWgenJS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# x-agent\n     2→\n     3→Every time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n     4→\n     5→## Why?\n     6→\n     7→Standard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n     8→\n     9→- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n    10→- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n    11→- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n    12→- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n    13→\n    14→## Available Agents\n    15→\n    16→| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n    17→|-------|-----------|-------|\n    18→| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n    19→| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n    20→| `gha-agent` | GitHub Actions | lint (actionlint) |\n    21→| `go-agent` | Go | fmt (gofmt), vet, staticcheck, test |\n    22→| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n    23→| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n    24→| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n    25→\n    26→## Quick Start\n    27→\n    28→### Install via curl\n    29→\n    30→```sh\n    31→curl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→### Install from local clone\n    35→\n    36→```sh\n    37→git clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\n    38→cd x-agent\n    39→sh install.sh\n    40→```\n    41→\n    42→Local installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\n    43→The installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\n    44→It also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n    45→\n    46→### Use directly (no install)\n    47→\n    48→```sh\n    49→# Rust project\n    50→path/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n    51→\n    52→# Node.js project\n    53→path/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n    54→\n    55→# Python project\n    56→path/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n    57→\n    58→# GitHub Actions project\n    59→path/to/x-agent/skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\n    60→\n    61→# Go project\n    62→path/to/x-agent/skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh\n    63→\n    64→# Terraform project\n    65→path/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n    66→```\n    67→\n    68→## Usage\n    69→\n    70→### bash-agent\n    71→\n    72→```sh\n    73→bash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\n    74→bash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\n    75→bash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\n    76→SHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n    77→```\n    78→\n    79→### cargo-agent\n    80→\n    81→```sh\n    82→cargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\n    83→cargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\n    84→cargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\n    85→cargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\n    86→cargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n    87→```\n    88→\n    89→### gha-agent\n    90→\n    91→```sh\n    92→gha-agent.sh              # lint all workflow files\n    93→gha-agent.sh lint         # actionlint check only\n    94→```\n    95→\n    96→`gha-agent` runs `actionlint` on `.github/workflows/*.yml` and `*.yaml` files. Reports SKIP when no workflows directory exists.\n    97→\n    98→### go-agent\n    99→\n   100→```sh\n   101→go-agent.sh                 # full suite: fmt + vet + staticcheck + test\n   102→go-agent.sh fmt             # gofmt check/fix\n   103→go-agent.sh vet             # go vet analysis\n   104→go-agent.sh test            # tests only\n   105→FMT_MODE=fix go-agent.sh fmt  # auto-fix formatting\n   106→```\n   107→\n   108→`go-agent` uses `gofmt` for formatting (auto-fix locally, check-only in CI), `go vet` for analysis, optional `staticcheck` for linting, and `go test` for tests.\n   109→\n   110→### npm-agent\n   111→\n   112→```sh\n   113→npm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\n   114→npm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n   115→npm-agent.sh test           # tests only\n   116→npm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→npm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n   120→\n   121→### py-agent\n   122→\n   123→```sh\n   124→py-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\n   125→py-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\n   126→py-agent.sh lint           # lint only\n   127→py-agent.sh test           # tests only\n   128→py-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n   129→```\n   130→\n   131→py-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n   132→\n   133→### terra-agent\n   134→\n   135→```sh\n   136→terra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\n   137→terra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\n   138→terra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\n   139→terra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\n   140→terra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\n   141→TERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\n   142→FMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n   143→```\n   144→\n   145→`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n   146→`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n   147→\n   148→## Environment Knobs\n   149→\n   150→All agents share the same pattern:\n   151→\n   152→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   153→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   154→| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n   155→| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n   156→| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n   157→\n   158→```sh\n   159→# Skip tests, keep logs\n   160→RUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n   161→\n   162→# Only run lint and typecheck\n   163→RUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n   164→```\n   165→\n   166→## Output Format\n   167→\n   168→```\n   169→------------------------------------------------------------\n   170→Step: clippy\n   171→Errors: 0\n   172→Warnings: 3\n   173→\n   174→Diagnostics (first 40 lines):\n   175→warning: unused variable `x`\n   176→warning: unused import `std::io`\n   177→warning: function `old_handler` is never used\n   178→\n   179→Result: PASS\n   180→Full JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\n   181→Lean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\n   182→Time: 4s\n   183→------------------------------------------------------------\n   184→Overall: PASS\n   185→Logs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→On **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n   189→\n   190→## Claude Code Skills\n   191→\n   192→The `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n   193→\n   194→- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n   195→- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n   196→- `/gha-agent` — run GitHub Actions workflow linting\n   197→- `/go-agent` — run Go checks\n   198→- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n   199→- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n   200→- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n   201→\n   202→## License\n   203→\n   204→MIT\n   205→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be0e30e7-8817-4b77-ad57-f2dbd38ea5b9","uuid":"892601b1-4b1e-4bca-972f-bc5986443b7a","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md","content":"# x-agent\n\nEvery time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.\n\n## Why?\n\nStandard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:\n\n- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`\n- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)\n- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed\n- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners\n\n## Available Agents\n\n| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |\n|-------|-----------|-------|\n| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |\n| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |\n| `gha-agent` | GitHub Actions | lint (actionlint) |\n| `go-agent` | Go | fmt (gofmt), vet, staticcheck, test |\n| `npm-agent` | Node.js | format, lint, typecheck, test, build |\n| `py-agent` | Python | format (ruff/black), lint (ruff/flake8), typecheck (mypy/pyright), test (pytest) |\n| `terra-agent` | Terraform | fmt (check/fix), safe init, plan-safe, validate, lint (tflint) |\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Install via curl\n\n```sh\ncurl -sSf https://raw.githubusercontent.com/codesoda/x-agent/main/install.sh | sh\n```\n\n### Install from local clone\n\n```sh\ngit clone git@github.com:codesoda/x-agent.git\ncd x-agent\nsh install.sh\n```\n\nLocal installs use symlinks so edits to the repo are immediately reflected.\nThe installer prompts for each x-agent skill so you can install only what you want.\nIt also prints a short AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md policy snippet you can copy/paste.\n\n### Use directly (no install)\n\n```sh\n# Rust project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/cargo-agent/scripts/cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Node.js project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/npm-agent/scripts/npm-agent.sh\n\n# Python project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/py-agent/scripts/py-agent.sh\n\n# GitHub Actions project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\n\n# Go project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/go-agent/scripts/go-agent.sh\n\n# Terraform project\npath/to/x-agent/skills/terra-agent/scripts/terra-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### bash-agent\n\n```sh\nbash-agent.sh              # full suite: syntax + lint\nbash-agent.sh syntax       # bash -n syntax check only\nbash-agent.sh lint         # shellcheck lint only\nSHELLCHECK_SEVERITY=error bash-agent.sh lint  # only errors, ignore warnings\n```\n\n### cargo-agent\n\n```sh\ncargo-agent.sh              # full suite: fmt + clippy + test\ncargo-agent.sh fmt          # format only\ncargo-agent.sh clippy       # clippy only\ncargo-agent.sh test         # tests only\ncargo-agent.sh test -p api  # tests in a specific crate\n```\n\n### gha-agent\n\n```sh\ngha-agent.sh              # lint all workflow files\ngha-agent.sh lint         # actionlint check only\n```\n\n`gha-agent` runs `actionlint` on `.github/workflows/*.yml` and `*.yaml` files. Reports SKIP when no workflows directory exists.\n\n### go-agent\n\n```sh\ngo-agent.sh                 # full suite: fmt + vet + staticcheck + test\ngo-agent.sh fmt             # gofmt check/fix\ngo-agent.sh vet             # go vet analysis\ngo-agent.sh test            # tests only\nFMT_MODE=fix go-agent.sh fmt  # auto-fix formatting\n```\n\n`go-agent` uses `gofmt` for formatting (auto-fix locally, check-only in CI), `go vet` for analysis, optional `staticcheck` for linting, and `go test` for tests.\n\n### npm-agent\n\n```sh\nnpm-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test + build\nnpm-agent.sh lint           # lint only\nnpm-agent.sh test           # tests only\nnpm-agent.sh typecheck      # type checking only\n```\n\nnpm-agent auto-detects your package manager (bun, pnpm, yarn, npm) and finds formatters/linters from package.json scripts or common tools (biome, eslint, prettier, tsc).\n\n### py-agent\n\n```sh\npy-agent.sh                # full suite: format + lint + typecheck + test\npy-agent.sh format         # format only (auto-fix locally, check in CI)\npy-agent.sh lint           # lint only\npy-agent.sh test           # tests only\npy-agent.sh test -k login  # tests matching \"login\"\n```\n\npy-agent auto-detects your runner (uv, poetry, or plain python) and finds tools (ruff, black, flake8, mypy, pyright, pytest).\n\n### terra-agent\n\n```sh\nterra-agent.sh                              # full suite: fmt(check) + validate + lint\nterra-agent.sh fmt-check                    # report formatting drift\nterra-agent.sh fmt-fix                      # auto-fix formatting\nterra-agent.sh init                         # safe non-mutating init\nterra-agent.sh plan-safe                    # safe non-mutating plan\nTERRAFORM_CHDIR=infra terra-agent.sh all    # run in infra/\nFMT_MODE=fix terra-agent.sh fmt             # fmt using env-selected mode\n```\n\n`terra-agent` init is safety-first by default: `-backend=false`, `-input=false`, `-get=false`, `-upgrade=false`, `-lockfile=readonly`, and temp `TF_DATA_DIR` so project files are not mutated.\n`terra-agent` plan-safe uses `-refresh=false`, `-lock=false`, and passes on detailed exit code `2` (changes detected).\n\n## Environment Knobs\n\nAll agents share the same pattern:\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `RUN_<STEP>` | `1` | Set to `0` to skip a step |\n| `MAX_LINES` | `40` | Max diagnostic lines printed per step |\n| `KEEP_DIR` | `0` | Set to `1` to keep temp log dir on success |\n\n```sh\n# Skip tests, keep logs\nRUN_TESTS=0 KEEP_DIR=1 cargo-agent.sh\n\n# Only run lint and typecheck\nRUN_FORMAT=0 RUN_TESTS=0 RUN_BUILD=0 npm-agent.sh\n```\n\n## Output Format\n\n```\n------------------------------------------------------------\nStep: clippy\nErrors: 0\nWarnings: 3\n\nDiagnostics (first 40 lines):\nwarning: unused variable `x`\nwarning: unused import `std::io`\nwarning: function `old_handler` is never used\n\nResult: PASS\nFull JSON: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.json\nLean diags: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123/clippy.diags.txt\nTime: 4s\n------------------------------------------------------------\nOverall: PASS\nLogs: /tmp/cargo-agent.abc123\n```\n\nOn **PASS**, temp logs are cleaned up automatically. On **FAIL** (or `KEEP_DIR=1`), logs are preserved and the path is printed so the agent can inspect them.\n\n## Claude Code Skills\n\nThe `skills/` directory contains Claude Code skill definitions. After installing, agents like Claude Code can invoke these as skills:\n\n- `/bash-agent` — run shell script checks\n- `/cargo-agent` — run Rust checks\n- `/gha-agent` — run GitHub Actions workflow linting\n- `/go-agent` — run Go checks\n- `/npm-agent` — run Node.js checks\n- `/py-agent` — run Python checks\n- `/terra-agent` — run Terraform checks/fixes\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n","numLines":205,"startLine":1,"totalLines":205}}}
