{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GTfywbLdmh9gapUBR5WD7o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Need to create the work summary first."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":155,"cache_read_input_tokens":72097,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":155},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be0e30e7-8817-4b77-ad57-f2dbd38ea5b9","uuid":"4dbc7f27-4271-4b02-9660-8262b597caaa"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GTfywbLdmh9gapUBR5WD7o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MRXfBiZ4HasaBux7FABpZU","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/work-summary.txt","content":"# Work Summary — Spec 06: helm-agent\n\n## What was implemented\n\nCreated the helm-agent — a lean Helm chart linter and template validator that runs `helm lint` and `helm template` on auto-detected chart directories.\n\n### Files created:\n- `skills/helm-agent/scripts/helm-agent.sh` — main agent script (~190 lines total, ~150 lines domain code)\n- `skills/helm-agent/SKILL.md` — trigger language, allowed-tools, and usage docs\n- `tests/helm-agent/clean/` — passing fixture (valid chart with Chart.yaml, values.yaml, templates/configmap.yaml)\n- `tests/helm-agent/issues/` — failing fixture (chart with `required` template function on missing value)\n- `tests/helm-agent/no-chart/` — skip fixture (empty directory, no Chart.yaml)\n\n### Files modified:\n- `install.sh` — added `helm-agent` to SKILLS, helm dep check, and snippet line\n- `README.md` — added helm-agent row in Available Agents table, usage section, direct-use example, and skill reference\n\n## Deviations from work plan\n\n- **Removed `scoped-clean` scenario**: The test runner (`run-scenarios.sh`) does not support passing arbitrary environment variables (like `CHANGED_FILES`) to agent scripts. The `EXTRA_ENV` feature doesn't exist. Rather than modifying the test runner (out of scope), removed this scenario. CHANGED_FILES scoping is implemented in the script but cannot be exercised via the existing test infrastructure.\n- **Item 12 (scope/skip edge cases)**: Implemented `no-chart` scenario for skip behavior. CHANGED_FILES scope testing deferred due to test runner limitation above.\n\n## Edge cases handled\n- No `Chart.yaml` found anywhere: returns `SKIP` with explicit reason for both lint and template steps\n- `CHART_DIR` set but no Chart.yaml at path: emits reason, SKIP behavior\n- `CHANGED_FILES` set but no chart-related files match: emits reason, SKIP\n- `CHANGED_FILES` filtering: only `.yaml`/`.yml`/`.tpl` files are considered chart-related\n- Chart root deduplication: multiple changed files in same chart produce single invocation\n- `--help`/`help`/`-h`: handled before `need helm` so it works without helm installed\n- Unknown commands: prints usage and exits 2\n- `RUN_LINT=0` / `RUN_TEMPLATE=0` in `all` mode: skips respective steps\n- `FAIL_FAST`: uses `should_continue()` from shared lib\n- Multiple charts: per-chart sequential iteration with indexed log files\n- Subchart exclusion: `find` excludes `*/charts/*` to avoid processing vendored subcharts\n\n## Tests written/run\n- `tests/helm-agent/clean/` — valid chart passes with exit 0\n- `tests/helm-agent/issues/` — chart with required field error fails with exit 1\n- `tests/helm-agent/no-chart/` — empty dir produces SKIP with exit 0\n- All 3 scenarios correctly SKIP when `helm` is not installed (REQUIRED_TOOLS gating)\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` passes on helm-agent.sh\n- Full suite: all 21 scenarios pass (including all existing agents), 0 failures\n\n## Known limitations\n- `CHANGED_FILES` splits on whitespace; paths with spaces are not supported (matches convention used by all other agents)\n- Scenario tests require `helm` to be installed to run the actual lint/template checks; they SKIP gracefully when missing\n- Test runner does not support EXTRA_ENV, so CHANGED_FILES scoping cannot be exercised in scenario tests\n\n## Feedback Closure Matrix\nNo prior review issues exist for this spec (first implementation).\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`: changed helm-agent from \"(to be added)\" to actual file path and description; updated tests/helm-agent description to reflect actual scenarios.\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\n- help-before-need: Parsed help flags before `need helm` so `--help` works without helm installed (pattern from bash-agent, go-agent, gha-agent)\n- Followed existing agent patterns (gha-agent) for file discovery, structured output, and scenario fixture format\n- Fixed shellcheck SC2221/SC2222 warning: `*.yaml` already covers `Chart.yaml` and `values.yaml` in case patterns\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- Verify `--help` works without helm installed\n- The issues fixture uses `required \"requiredField must be set\"` on a missing value which should fail deterministically\n- Verify SKIP behavior when no `Chart.yaml` exists (no-chart scenario)\n- `CHANGED_FILES` scoping correctly filters `.yaml`/`.yml`/`.tpl` and finds parent Chart.yaml\n- Chart root deduplication via `seen` variable prevents duplicate runs\n- Subchart directories (`*/charts/*`) are excluded from recursive discovery\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":155,"cache_read_input_tokens":72097,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":155},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be0e30e7-8817-4b77-ad57-f2dbd38ea5b9","uuid":"c1b632de-1306-48a1-8899-c9f02298e0f4"}
